# fast-secrets API v2 examples (JetBrains HTTP Client / VS Code REST Client)

@base = http://127.0.0.1:8000

### Health check
GET {{base}}/healthz
Accept: application/json

### Typed metadata for all tools
GET {{base}}/api/tools
Accept: application/json

### Five time-sortable UUID v7 values
POST {{base}}/api/tools/uuid/run
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "inputs": {},
  "options": {"version": 7, "uppercase": false, "hyphens": true},
  "count": 5
}

### Password policy output as newline-delimited text
POST {{base}}/api/tools/password_policy/run
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/x-ndjson

{
  "inputs": {},
  "options": {
    "length": 24,
    "min_lowercase": 2,
    "min_uppercase": 2,
    "min_digits": 2,
    "min_symbols": 2,
    "exclude_ambiguous": true
  },
  "count": 3
}

### Inspect and verify a JWT (replace token and secret)
POST {{base}}/api/tools/jwt_verify/run
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "inputs": {
    "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJ1c2VyXzEyMyJ9.invalid",
    "secret": "replace-me"
  },
  "options": {
    "allowed_algorithms": ["HS256"],
    "leeway": 30
  },
  "count": 1
}

### Mixed batch (partial failures are returned per item)
POST {{base}}/api/batch
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "requests": [
    {"tool": "uuid", "inputs": {}, "options": {"version": 7}, "count": 2},
    {"tool": "hex", "inputs": {}, "options": {"nbytes": 16}, "count": 2},
    {"tool": "timestamp", "inputs": {"value": "1704067200000"}, "options": {"output_timezones": ["UTC", "America/Mexico_City"]}, "count": 1}
  ]
}
